<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Rume"
  subtitle="A contemplative space for collecting and revisiting personal memories."
  category="Mobile App"
  year="2025"
  description="Rume — a contemplative memory collection app by Mackenzie Hart"
  role="Product Designer"
  duration="10 weeks"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Rume is a mobile app designed for people who want to hold onto the texture
      of their lives — not just the facts, but the feeling. Inspired by the
      Japanese concept of <em>mono no aware</em>, it invites slow, intentional
      capture rather than the reflexive archiving that dominates social media.
    </p>
    <p>
      The challenge was to create something that felt like a private ritual,
      not a productivity tool. Every interaction needed to be unhurried.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>"How might we help people revisit memory without the weight of a timeline?"</p>
